# Recruiter-X Backend Status & TODO List

This document acts as the master checklist of all backend features, detailing what has been successfully built and what remains to be implemented.

---

## 1. Environment & Setup

- [x] **Project Structure Setup**: Created `api/`, `frontend/`, `workers/`, `docs/` directories.
- [x] **FastAPI Foundation**: [index.py](file:///d:/2026/college%20pro/hack/api/index.py) configured with standard logs, health check, and CORS configuration.
- [x] **Configuration Loading**: [config.py](file:///d:/2026/college%20pro/hack/api/config.py) configured to load credentials and variables via Pydantic from `.env`.
- [x] **Dependency Specification**: `requirements.txt` listing all Python packages.
- [x] **Celery App Configuration**: [celery_app.py](file:///d:/2026/college%20pro/hack/api/celery_app.py) initialized with priority task queues and rate limit definitions.
- [x] **Docker Compose Runner**: `docker-compose.yml` for running local redis, API, and workers in development.

---

## 2. Database Schema & Supabase Integration

- [x] **Schema Definition**: [schema.sql](file:///d:/2026/college%20pro/hack/api/database/schema.sql) defining tables, indexes, and custom enum types.
- [x] **Row-Level Security (RLS)**: Policies written for isolation of organization/tenant data in the SQL schema.
- [x] **Supabase Client Setup**: [supabase_client.py](file:///d:/2026/college%20pro/hack/api/services/supabase_client.py) service-role client initialized to bypass RLS for background processes.
- [x] **Schema Migration**: Created [migrate_db.py](file:///d:/2026/college%20pro/hack/api/scratch/migrate_db.py) to automate raw schema script execution on the database (configure DATABASE_URL in `api/.env` and execute).
- [x] **Private Storage Bucket Setup**: Integrated bucket provisioning via Supabase SDK into [migrate_db.py](file:///d:/2026/college%20pro/hack/api/scratch/migrate_db.py) (configure SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY in `api/.env` and execute).

---

## 3. Core LLM Clients & Layer

- [x] **Standard Client Clients**: 
  - [Gemini Client](file:///d:/2026/college%20pro/hack/api/llm/providers/gemini.py) supporting structured JSON output via `generate_content_async`.
  - [OpenAI Client](file:///d:/2026/college%20pro/hack/api/llm/providers/openai.py) supporting Pydantic parsing natively.
  - [Anthropic Client](file:///d:/2026/college%20pro/hack/api/llm/providers/anthropic.py) enforcing structure via tools calling overrides.
- [x] **LLM Router**: [router.py](file:///d:/2026/college%20pro/hack/api/llm/router.py) managing token budget validation, default temperature settings by task type, client orchestration, and response schema parsing.
- [x] **Error Normalization**: Custom exceptions in [errors.py](file:///d:/2026/college%20pro/hack/api/utils/errors.py) catching and mapping diverse API provider exceptions (timeouts, rate limits, authentication issues).

